<subSubSection id="C3508AD2FFA63C5CFF6BB8E5FE2B82DC" box="[151,445,1712,1739]" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BF5D959FFA63C5CFF6BB8E5FE2B82DC" blockId="0.[151,445,1712,1739]" box="[151,445,1712,1739]" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">
<heading id="D0BD6E35FFA63C5CFF6BB8E5FE2B82DC" bold="true" box="[151,445,1712,1739]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA63C5CFF6BB8E5FE2B82DC" bold="true" box="[151,445,1712,1739]" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA63C5CFEE2B8E4FE2B82DC" baseAuthorityName="ThripsWiki" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[286,445,1712,1739]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA63C5CFEE2B8E4FE2B82DC" bold="true" box="[286,445,1712,1739]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">Teuchothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3508AD2FFA63C5DFF6BB8ADFD9E87DE" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="239" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF5D959FFA63C5DFF6BB8ADFE08862A" blockId="0.[151,1437,1784,2027]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1437,150,969]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="239" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">
This genus is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA63C5CFE1BB8ADFDD88304" authorityName="Uzel" authorityYear="1895" box="[487,590,1785,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA63C5CFE1BB8ADFDD88304" box="[487,590,1785,1811]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-lineage (Mound &amp; Marullo 1996), in which all species usually have a single sense cone on antennal segment III and three sense cones on segment IV. This condition is generally consistent among several hundred species of this lineage, whereas three of the five species currently listed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA63C5CFAF7B915FA0A834C" baseAuthorityName="ThripsWiki" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1291,1436,1857,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA63C5CFAF7B915FA0A834C" box="[1291,1436,1857,1883]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">Teuchothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA63C5CFF2AB931FE138368" box="[214,389,1893,1919]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
are here recognised as having the sense cone numbers irregular. Amongst these species one available female 
<typeStatus id="54F167FBFFA63C5CFEABB9DDFE2183B4" box="[343,439,1929,1955]" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA63C5CFE22B9DDFDD983B5" authorityName="Bournier" authorityYear="1993" box="[478,591,1929,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA63C5CFE22B9DDFDD983B5" box="[478,591,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">T. ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two sense cones on segment III of one antenna (but not both), a condition that is likely to be an aberration. But segment IV of three available 
<typeStatus id="54F167FBFFA63C5CFC51B9F9FB8E83D0" box="[941,1048,1965,1991]" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA63C5CFBC7B9F9FB3A83D1" authorityName="Bournier" authorityYear="1993" box="[1083,1196,1965,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA63C5CFBC7B9F9FB3A83D1" box="[1083,1196,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="238">T. ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears two large sense cones, and a similar condition had been found on 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA63C5CFD37B985FCA683FC" box="[715,816,2001,2027]" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" type="male">14 males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA63C5CFC94B985FC7283FC" box="[872,996,2001,2027]" pageId="0" pageNumber="238" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
of this species collected more recently (LAM5607). A similar condition was also observed on 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA73C5DFCEEBEC3FCEF84A6" box="[786,889,151,177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="54F167FBFFA73C5DFC7FBEC3FC7584A6" box="[899,995,151,177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFBF0BEC3FBED84A6" baseAuthorityName="Bournier" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[1036,1147,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kraussi">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFBF0BEC3FBED84A6" box="[1036,1147,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">T. kraussi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA73C5DFB49BEC3FAA584A6" box="[1205,1331,151,177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="54F167FBFFA73C5DFAC0BEC3FA0A84A6" box="[1340,1436,151,177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFF45BEEFFEFE84C3" authorityName="Bournier" authorityYear="1993" box="[185,360,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noumeaensis">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFF45BEEFFEFE84C3" box="[185,360,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">T. noumeaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A further variation noted occurred on 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA73C5DFCCEBEEFFC5484C2" box="[818,962,187,213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" type="female">four females</specimenCount>
identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFB9FBEEFFB4184C3" authorityName="Bournier" authorityYear="1993" box="[1123,1239,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFB9FBEEFFB4184C3" box="[1123,1239,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">T. ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(LAM5607) and 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA73C5DFF6BBE8BFE8584EE" box="[151,275,223,249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="54F167FBFFA73C5DFEE7BE8BFEED84EE" box="[283,379,223,249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFE5EBE8BFDD984EF" authorityName="Bournier" authorityYear="1993" box="[418,591,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noumeaensis">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFE5EBE8BFDD984EF" box="[418,591,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">T. noumeaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; These 
<specimenCount id="9D4C12D0FFA73C5DFD54BE8BFCC684EE" box="[680,848,223,249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" type="generic">five specimens</specimenCount>
each had two large sense cones on one antenna, but two large and one smaller sense cones on the other antenna. These variations from the typical condition amongst members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFEB6BF73FE278556" authorityName="Uzel" authorityYear="1895" box="[330,433,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFEB6BF73FE278556" box="[330,433,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-lineage of three sense cones on antennal segment IV will need further consideration in the future. Detailed examination of both antennae on every individual specimen is needed to recognise this intraspecific variation in sense cone number, and the fact that it is recorded for so few species in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFBABBF3BFB28859E" authorityName="Uzel" authorityYear="1895" box="[1111,1214,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFBABBF3BFB28859E" box="[1111,1214,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-lineage may be due to lack of detailed study. Similar intraspecific variation in the number of antennal sense cones is recorded of some species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFEF7BFE3FE3F85C6" authorityName="Mound &amp; Walker" authorityYear="1986" box="[267,425,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Deplorothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFEF7BFE3FE3F85C6" box="[267,425,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Deplorothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFE0FBFE3FD1285C6" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1836" box="[499,644,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Phlaeothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFE0FBFE3FD1285C6" box="[499,644,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Phlaeothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-lineage (Mound &amp; Tree 2016), and also of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFB9ABFE3FACE85C6" baseAuthorityName="Jones" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1126,1368,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Karnyothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFB9ABFE3FACE85C6" box="[1126,1368,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Karnyothrips flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFF6BBF8FFE7D85E1" authority="(Okajima 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Okajima" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[151,491,475,502]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Haplothripini">
Haplothripini (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDBA4A8FFA73C5DFEC1BF8FFE7585E1" author="Okajima" box="[317,483,475,502]" firstAuthor="Okajima" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" refId="ref3795" refString="Okajima, S. (2006) The Suborder Tubulifera (Thysanoptera). The Insects of Japan. Vol. 2. The Entomological Society of Japan, Touka Shobo Co. Ltd., Fukuoka, 720 pp." type="book" year="2006">Okajima 2006</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, one of the species listed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFC7EBF8FFB8585E2" baseAuthorityName="ThripsWiki" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[898,1043,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFC7EBF8FFB8585E2" box="[898,1043,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Teuchothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA73C5DFBA5BF8FFA9F85E2" box="[1113,1289,475,501]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFAE8BF8FFA0385E2" baseAuthorityName="Bianchi" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1300,1429,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pacificus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFAE8BF8FFA0385E2" box="[1300,1429,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">T. pacificus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has two large sense cones on both segments III and IV, and as discussed below this species is here transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFF1CBC77FE0E862A" authorityName="Bagnall" authorityYear="1928" box="[224,408,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Neocecidothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFF1CBC77FE0E862A" box="[224,408,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Neocecidothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5D959FFA73C5DFF3BBC13FD9E87DE" blockId="1.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">
The species included in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFE2ABC13FDF18676" baseAuthorityName="ThripsWiki" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[470,615,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFE2ABC13FDF18676" box="[470,615,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Teuchothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are closely similar in structure to species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFBA7BC13FB548676" authorityName="Uzel" authorityYear="1895" box="[1115,1218,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFBA7BC13FB548676" box="[1115,1218,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The only recorded differentiating character states are that 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFDB3BC3FFD768692" box="[591,736,619,645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFDB3BC3FFD768692" box="[591,736,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Teuchothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species tend to have antennal segment VIII short and broadly based, and on the pronotum at least one of the five pairs of major setae is not elongate. In contrast, species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFF6BBCE7FF6886DA" authorityName="Uzel" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,254,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Liothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFF6BBCE7FF6886DA" box="[151,254,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Liothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have antennal segment VIII longer and constricted basally, and all five pairs of pronotal major setae are elongate (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDBA4A8FFA73C5DFEF9BC83FE0B86E6" author="Mound" box="[261,413,727,753]" firstAuthor="Mound" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" pagination="41 - 60" refId="ref3509" refString="Mound, L. A. (2008) Identification and host associations of some Thysanoptera Phlaeothripinae described from Australia pre- 1930. Zootaxa, 1714 (1), 41 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1714.1.5" type="journal article" year="2008">Mound 2008</bibRefCitation>
). With the transfer here of one species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFC8FBC83FBBD86E6" authorityName="Bagnall" authorityYear="1928" box="[883,1067,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Neocecidothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFC8FBC83FBBD86E6" box="[883,1067,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Neocecidothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there are 25 species listed under 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFF6BBCAFFD948702" authority="(ThripsWiki 2021)" baseAuthorityName="ThripsWiki" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[151,514,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFF6BBCAFFEBE8702" box="[151,296,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Teuchothrips</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDBA4A8FFA73C5DFECABCAFFE6D8702" accessDate="2021-07-08" author="ThripsWiki" box="[310,507,763,789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" publicationUrl="http://thrips.info/wiki/" refId="ref3836" refString="ThripsWiki (2021) ThripsWiki - providing information on the World's thrips. Available from: http: // thrips. info / wiki / (accessed 8 July 2021)" title="ThripsWiki - providing information on the World's thrips" type="url" year="2021">ThripsWiki 2021</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, including four from 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA73C5DFD0CBCAFFC368702" box="[752,928,763,789]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
. Of the remaining species, 13 are known only from 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA73C5DFF28BD4BFEA8872E" box="[212,318,799,825]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Australia</collectingCountry>
, including the 
<typeStatus id="54F167FBFFA73C5DFE18BD4BFD82872E" box="[484,532,799,825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">type</typeStatus>
species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDBA4A8FFA73C5DFD80BD4BFC85872E" author="Mound" box="[636,787,799,825]" firstAuthor="Mound" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" pagination="41 - 60" refId="ref3509" refString="Mound, L. A. (2008) Identification and host associations of some Thysanoptera Phlaeothripinae described from Australia pre- 1930. Zootaxa, 1714 (1), 41 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1714.1.5" type="journal article" year="2008">Mound 2008</bibRefCitation>
). One species was described from New 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA73C5DFB29BD4BFABF872E" box="[1237,1321,799,825]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, two from 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA73C5DFF6BBD17FE8E874A" box="[151,280,835,861]" name="Philippines" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, two from Java, two from 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA73C5DFDC4BD17FD31874A" box="[568,679,835,861]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, and one from 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA73C5DFCB5BD17FC10874A" box="[841,902,835,861]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">India</collectingCountry>
. Each of the four species from 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA73C5DFB24BD17FA12874A" box="[1240,1412,835,861]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
is considered to be distinct from all of the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4AA2DAFFA73C5DFD3BBD33FCCE8796" baseAuthorityName="ThripsWiki" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[711,856,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Teuchothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93E054BFFA73C5DFD3BBD33FCCE8796" box="[711,856,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Teuchothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from 
<collectingCountry id="F35D99C9FFA73C5DFC10BD33FBC08796" box="[1004,1110,871,897]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Australia</collectingCountry>
, including many undescribed species in the collections at CSIRO, Canberra. This is not surprising, in view of the apparent specificity to particular plants by members of this genus.
</paragraph>
